<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - ADJUSTMENTS - CAB AIR SUSPENSION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601817" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAB AIR SUSPENSION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure the design height of the air spring(s). The height should be 5 inches &#177; 1/8 (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601899">Figure 99</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1601899" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601899" filename="../figg16/G1601899.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="152px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 99. Air Spring Design Height</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To change the height, loosen jam nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16018a0">Item 1, Figure 100</hotlnk>) at one end of the valve linkage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16018a0">Item 2, Figure 100</hotlnk>) and adjust accordingly. Tighten the jam nut on
                the valve linkage. The valve arm assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16018a0">Item 3, Figure 100</hotlnk>) has a slot (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f16018a0">Item 4, Figure 100</hotlnk>) which will allow for coarse adjustment also.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f16018a0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g16018a0" filename="../figg16/G16018a0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 100. Adjust Air Spring Height</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. JAM NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. VALVE LINKAGE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. VALVE ARM ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SLOT FOR COARSE ADJUSTMENT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. AIR SUPPLY AIR LINE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. AIR LINE TO AIR SPRING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
